  <section class="hero is-medium" style="background-image: url('/assets/hero/hero-tech.png')">
    <div class="hero-body">
      <div class="container">
        <h1 class="primary-text">Take a deep-dive and understand<br>LTO Network on a technical level.</h1>
        <div class="buttons btn-container">
          <a href="https://docs.ltonetwork.com" class="button"><p class="dark-indigo">Explore documentation</p></a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>

<div class="section-container cutout-top">
  <section class="section secondary no-padding">
    <div class="promo-numbers c">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="item">
            <p class="promo-head deep-lavender">1M+</p>
            <p class="promo-desc dark-indigo">easy integration</p>
        </div>
        <div class="item">
          <p class="promo-head deep-lavender">30K+</p>
          <p class="promo-desc dark-indigo">transactions per day</p>
        </div>
        <div class="item">
          <p class="promo-head deep-lavender">100+</p>
          <p class="promo-desc dark-indigo">LTO nodes</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>

<div class="section-container cutin-top-alt cutout-bottom">
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="has-text-centered section-title">Functional layers</h2>
      <div class="columns is-vcentered inverted-mobile has-margin-top-40">
       <div class="column is-4">
            <div class="content">
                <strong class="muted">Decentralized applications</strong>
                <p class="muted">Organizations participate on distributed applications via their own node, without a central system.</p>
                <strong class="muted">Distributed data processing</strong>
                <p class="muted">Data is shared peer-to-peer between the nodes of specific participants, never with the whole network.</p>
                <strong class="muted">Blockchain</strong>
                <p class="muted">All nodes are connected via the public blockchain, which is used for consensus and data integrity.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="column">
          <img src="/assets/why-lto.png" alt="Functional Layers">
          </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>

<div class="section-container cutout-bottom-alt" id="why-hybrid-blockchain-section">
  <section class="section alt p-top-l neg-m-top-m">
    <div class="section-body" style="position:relative;">
      <div class="public-chain" id="public-chain"></div>
      <div class="private-chain" id="private-chain"></div>
        <div class="container">
            <div class="columns has-text-centered-mobile">
                <div class="column is-5-desktop">
                    <h2 class="section-title deep-lavender">Hybrid blockchain</h2>
                        <div class="content">
                            <p class="muted">LTO Network allows two or more businesses to share and agree upon sequences of events. This is done peer-to-peer, without relying on an authoritative party.</p>
                            <p class="muted">The limited number of parties involved present a challenge when dealing with conflicts. A majority, if it can be formed at all, can't provide an unbiased decision.</p>
                            <p class="muted">Rather than re-introducing authorization on the network, consensus is reached by leveraging on our public proof-of-stake blockchain. The hash of private events are anchored on the public chain.</p>
                            <p class="muted">Blocks of the public chain have a specific height and transactions within a block are also ordered. This provides a globally recognized sequence of events, which is used to reach consensus on the private chain.</p>
                            <p class="muted"><em>A hybrid blockchain means private data, public consensus.</em></p>
                        </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>

<div class="section-container">
  <section class="section relative tertiary p-top-l neg-m-top-m">
           <div class="section-body">
           <div class="container">
            <h2 class="section-title has-text-centered">
          Inside an LTO Node
        </h2>
        <h3 class="small-subtitle has-text-centered">
          Select any component to learn more about our setup
        </h3>
            <div class="tiles-container">
        <div class="tiles node-card">
          <div class="tile-group rest-api-layer-container">
            <span>Rest Api Layer</span>
            <div class="tile lto-node" id="api-gateway-tile">
              <span class="title is-size-6 dark-indigo">Api Gateway</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="tile-group application-layer-container">
            <span>Application Layer</span>
            <div class="tile lto-node" id="event-chain-service-tile">
              <span class="title is-size-6 dark-indigo">Event Chain Service</span>
            </div>
            <div class="tile fit lto-node" id="workflow-engine-tile">
              <span class="title is-size-6 dark-indigo">Additional services</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="tile-group private-chain-layer-container">
            <span>Private Chain Layer</span>
            <div class="tile lto-node" id="queuer-service-tile">
              <span class="title is-size-6 dark-indigo">Queuer</span>
            </div>
            <div class="tile lto-node" id="dispatcher-service-tile">
              <span class="title is-size-6 dark-indigo">Dispatcher</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="tile-group global-chain-layer-container">
            <span>Global Chain Layer</span>
            <div class="tile lto-node" id="proof-engine-tile">
              <span class="title is-size-6 dark-indigo">Anchoring Service</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tile-sidebar is-4 is-parent is-vertical node-card">
          <article class="tile inside-node">
            <div class="content" id="api-gateway-content" style="display: none;">
              <p class="tile-title is-size-4 title dark-indigo">API Gateway</p>
              <div class="tile-content">
               <p class="muted">
                 The API Gateway is an HTTP server which proxies all the requests to the right service within the node.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="content" id="event-chain-service-content" style="display: block;">
              <p class="tile-title is-size-4 title dark-indigo">Event Chain Service</p>
              <div class="tile-content">
               <p class="muted">
                   The Event Chain Service holds all ad hoc private blockchains an organization is involved in.</p>
                <ul class="muted is-size-6">
                  <li>One node holds many ad hoc blockchains. (similar to git repositories).</li>
                  <li>Fully decoupled.</li>
                  <li>Configurable allowing it to interact to any microservice added to the application layer.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="content" id="workflow-engine-content" style="display: none;">
              <p class="tile-title is-size-4 title dark-indigo">Additional services</p>
              <div class="tile-content">
               <p class="muted">
                   Additional services can be added to the node for running decentralized applications;</p>
                <ul class="muted is-size-6">
                  <li>The Workflow engine runs processes modelled as deterministic finite state machines.</li>
                  <li>Monitored data distribution helps reach (GDPR) compliance when sharing data across organizations.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="content" id="queuer-service-content" style="display: none;">
              <p class="tile-title is-size-4 title dark-indigo">Queuer</p>
              <div class="tile-content">
               <p class="muted">
                   The Queuer Service provides a REST API to queue events on the Message Queue.</p>
                <ul class="muted is-size-6">
                 <li>RabbitMQ message queue which uses shoveling to distribute events to other nodes.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="content" id="dispatcher-service-content" style="display: none;">
              <p class="tile-title is-size-4 title dark-indigo">Dispatcher</p>
              <div class="tile-content">
               <p class="muted">
                 The Dispatcher Service parses messages from the message queue and pushes them to right service within the node.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="content" id="proof-engine-content" style="display: none;">
              <p class="tile-title is-size-4 title dark-indigo">Anchoring</p>
              <div class="tile-content">
               <p class="muted">
                 This node connects the LTO platform to the LTO public blockchain that is responsible for securing data and events through anchoring.
               </p>
                <ul class="muted is-size-6">
                  <li>Use industry standard hashing (SHA2) and cryptography (ED25519) algorithms</li>
                  <li>The NG protocol provides fast tx acknowledgement, typically within 3 seconds.</li>
                  <li>The public chain is optimized for storing hashes and doesn't provide general purpose functionality.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>

          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
        </div>
      </div>
  </section>
</div>

